Q. Given a decinal number N, convert it to binary number.

We can convert a number to binary by simply diving the number by 2 and if the reminder is 1,
append 1 to the string and if the reminder is 0, append 0 to the ans string.
Lastly, reverse the string.

string convertToBinary(int n){
  res = "";

  while(n!= 1){
    if(n%2==1) res+= '1';
    else res= += '0';
    n= n/2;
  }
  reverse(res);
  return res;
}
